I"è<p>This post should display a large hero image at the top of a page.</p>

<p>This post tests a horizontal image using the following YAML Front Matter:</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="na">image</span><span class="pi">:</span>
  <span class="na">path</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">/images/eder-oliveira-180877.jpg</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Hero images can also be assigned more succinctly when <code class="highlighter-rouge">thumbnail</code> or <code class="highlighter-rouge">caption</code> are not used.</p>

<div class="language-yaml highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="na">image</span><span class="pi">:</span> <span class="s">/images/eder-oliveira-180877.jpg</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Tall images will push content down the page. <code class="highlighter-rouge">1600 x 600</code> is a good middle-ground size to aim for.</p>
